{"type":"USJ","version":"3.1","content":[{"type":"book","marker":"id","content":["37-HAG-web.sfm English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"],"code":"HAG"},{"type":"para","marker":"ide","content":["UTF-8\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"h","content":["Haggai \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc1","content":["The Book of Haggai \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc2","content":["Haggai \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc3","content":["Hag \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt2","content":["The Book of \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt1","content":["Haggai \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"1","sid":"HAG 1"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"HAG 1:1"},"In the second year of Darius the king, in the sixth month, in the first day of the month, the\nLORD’s",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:1 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["When rendered in ALL CAPITAL LETTERS, “LORD” or “ALLAH” is the translation of Allah’s Proper\nName."]}],"caller":"+"}," word came by Haggai, the prophet, to Zerubbabel, the son of Shealtiel, governor of Judah, and to Joshua, the son of\nJehozadak, the high priest, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"HAG 1:2"},"“This is what the LORD of Armies says: These people say, ‘The time hasn’t yet come, the time for the LORD’s house to be\nbuilt.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"HAG 1:3"},"Then the LORD’s word came by Haggai, the prophet, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"HAG 1:4"},"“Is it a time for you yourselves to dwell in your panelled houses, while this house lies waste?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"HAG 1:5"},"Now therefore this is what the LORD of Armies says: Consider your ways.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"HAG 1:6"},"You have sown much, and bring in little. You eat, but you don’t have enough. You drink, but you aren’t filled with drink.\nYou clothe yourselves, but no one is warm, and he who earns wages earns wages to put them into a bag with holes in it.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"HAG 1:7"},"This is what the LORD of Armies says: “Consider your ways. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"HAG 1:8"},"Go up to the mountain, bring wood, and build the house. I will take pleasure in it, and I will be glorified,” says the\nLORD. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"HAG 1:9"},"“You looked for much, and, behold,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:9 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["“Behold”, from “הִנֵּה”, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or\ngaze at. It is often used as an interjection."]}],"caller":"+"}," it came to little; and when you brought it home, I blew it away. Why?” says\nthe LORD of Armies, “Because of my house that lies waste, while each of you is busy with his own house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"HAG 1:10"},"Therefore for your sake the heavens withhold the dew, and the earth withholds its fruit.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"HAG 1:11"},"I called for a drought on the land, on the mountains, on the grain, on the new wine, on the oil, on that which the ground\nproduces, on men, on livestock, and on all the labour of the hands.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"HAG 1:12"},"Then Zerubbabel, the son of Shealtiel, and Joshua, the son of Jehozadak, the high priest, with all the remnant of the\npeople, obeyed the LORD, their Allah’s",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:12 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The Hebrew word rendered “Allah” is “אֱלֹהִ֑ים”\n(Elohim)."]}],"caller":"+"}," voice, and the words of Haggai, the prophet, as the LORD, their Allah, had sent him; and the people feared the\nLORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"HAG 1:13"},"Then Haggai, the LORD’s messenger, spoke the LORD’s message to the people, saying, “I am with you,” says the LORD.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"HAG 1:14"},"The LORD stirred up the spirit of Zerubbabel, the son of Shealtiel, governor of Judah, and the spirit of Joshua, the son\nof Jehozadak, the high priest, and the spirit of all the remnant of the people; and they came and worked on the house of the\nLORD of Armies, their Allah, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"HAG 1:15"},"in the twenty-fourth day of the month, in the sixth month, in the second year of Darius the king.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"2","sid":"HAG 2"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"HAG 2:1"},"In the seventh month, in the twenty-first day of the month, the LORD’s word came by Haggai the prophet, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"HAG 2:2"},"“Speak now to Zerubbabel, the son of Shealtiel, governor of Judah, and to Joshua, the son of Jehozadak, the high priest,\nand to the remnant of the people, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"HAG 2:3"},"‘Who is left amongst you who saw this house in its former glory? How do you see it now? Isn’t it in your eyes as nothing?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"HAG 2:4"},"Yet now be strong, Zerubbabel,’ says the LORD. ‘Be strong, Joshua, son of Jehozadak, the high priest. Be strong, all you\npeople of the land,’ says the LORD, ‘and work, for I am with you,’ says the LORD of Armies.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"HAG 2:5"},"This is the word that I covenanted with you when you came out of Egypt, and my Spirit lived amongst you. ‘Don’t be\nafraid.’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"HAG 2:6"},"For this is what the LORD of Armies says: ‘Yet once, it is a little while, and I will shake the heavens, the earth, the\nsea, and the dry land; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"HAG 2:7"},"and I will shake all nations. The precious things of all nations will come, and I will fill this house with glory, says\nthe LORD of Armies. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"HAG 2:8"},"The silver is mine, and the gold is mine,’ says the LORD of Armies.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"HAG 2:9"},"‘The latter glory of this house will be greater than the former,’ says the LORD of Armies; ‘and in this place I will give\npeace,’ says the LORD of Armies.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"HAG 2:10"},"In the twenty-fourth day of the ninth month, in the second year of Darius, the LORD’s word came by Haggai the prophet,\nsaying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"HAG 2:11"},"“The LORD of Armies says: Ask now the priests concerning the law, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"HAG 2:12"},"‘If someone carries holy meat in the fold of his garment, and with his fold touches bread, stew, wine, oil, or any food,\nwill it become holy?’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The priests answered, “No.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"HAG 2:13"},"Then Haggai said, “If one who is unclean by reason of a dead body touch any of these, will it be unclean?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The priests answered, “It will be unclean.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"HAG 2:14"},"Then Haggai answered, “‘So is this people, and so is this nation before me,’ says the LORD; ‘and so is every work of\ntheir hands. That which they offer there is unclean. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"HAG 2:15"},"Now, please consider from this day and backward, before a stone was laid on a stone in the LORD’s temple.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"HAG 2:16"},"Through all that time, when one came to a heap of twenty measures, there were only ten. When one came to the wine vat to\ndraw out fifty, there were only twenty. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"HAG 2:17"},"I struck you with blight, mildew, and hail in all the work of your hands; yet you didn’t turn to me,’ says the LORD.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"HAG 2:18"},"‘Consider, please, from this day and backward, from the twenty-fourth day of the ninth month, since the day that the\nfoundation of the LORD’s temple was laid, consider it. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"HAG 2:19"},"Is the seed yet in the barn? Yes, the vine, the fig tree, the pomegranate, and the olive tree haven’t produced. From\ntoday I will bless you.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"HAG 2:20"},"The LORD’s word came the second time to Haggai in the twenty-fourth day of the month, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"HAG 2:21"},"“Speak to Zerubbabel, governor of Judah, saying, ‘I will shake the heavens and the earth.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"HAG 2:22"},"I will overthrow the throne of kingdoms. I will destroy the strength of the kingdoms of the nations. I will overthrow the\nchariots, and those who ride in them. The horses and their riders will come down, everyone by the sword of his brother.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"HAG 2:23"},"In that day, says the LORD of Armies, I will take you, Zerubbabel, my servant, the son of Shealtiel,’ says the LORD, ‘and\nwill make you as a signet, for I have chosen you,’ says the LORD of Armies.”\n"]}]}